H0.text: Chickens are the animal that does NOT lay eggs among the animals listed.

H3.text: Turtles are the animal that does not lay eggs.

A4.text: A hen bred for laying can produce over 300 eggs per year.

A5.text: Dogs bear their litters roughly 58 to 68 days after fertilization, with an average of 63 days, although the length of gestation can vary.
